		       <h2>PHP Issues</h2>
		       <p>here are some issues developers may encounter regarding php</p>
					<ul>
					<md-block>
					- web-server shutting down => the web server may shutdown upon visting a page that references a external stylesheet in directory form, you must use inline css using ```< style >```

					- the web server may shutdown upon running => root level console commands avoid running programs or root level commands for both security and stability reasons

					- archived pages may give a unsecure warning => this is because archived pages use a slightly outdated version of PHP.
					</md-block>
				</ul>
